#: inc/onboarding.php
msgid "Mainframe is currently in safe mode — all your WordPress content is publicly accessible at its standard URLs. This is intentional: it lets you verify your content before switching."
msgstr ""

#: inc/onboarding.php
msgid "When your consuming app (Next.js, Nuxt, SvelteKit, etc.) is ready to be the only public face of your site, apply the headless defaults below. Each setting is reversible from this page at any time."
msgstr ""

#: inc/onboarding.php
msgid "Redirect all public content routes to home"
msgstr ""

#: inc/onboarding.php
msgid "Posts, pages, and archives redirect visitors to the home page by default. Individual posts can still be set to \"Show content\" via the per-post meta box."
msgstr ""

#: inc/onboarding.php
msgid "Discourage search engine indexing"
msgstr ""

#: inc/onboarding.php
msgid "Tells search engines not to index this WordPress backend. Your consuming frontend should handle SEO instead."
msgstr ""

#: inc/onboarding.php
msgid "Disable comments and pingbacks on new posts"
msgstr ""

#: inc/onboarding.php
msgid "Comments can still be enabled per-post and are fully accessible via the REST API when a post has comment_status = open."
msgstr ""

#: inc/onboarding.php
msgid "Use flat upload folder structure"
msgstr ""

#: inc/onboarding.php
msgid "Disables year/month subfolders in wp-content/uploads/. Automatically skipped if year-based folders already exist."
msgstr ""

#: inc/onboarding.php
msgid "Set a custom login URL slug"
msgstr ""

#: inc/onboarding.php
msgid "Blocks /wp-login.php and serves login at your chosen slug. Leave blank to keep /wp-login.php active."
